            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>Canute R. Matson became the sheriff of Cook County late in 1886, following the Haymarket Riot and the subsequent trial of eight men charged with murdering a policeman during the riot. This collection contains photocopies of Matson&#039;s official correspondence from this period, including petition for a writ of error, instructions from Gov. Richard J. Oglesby regarding the commutation of the sentences of two of the defendants, personal statements from the defendants&#039; lawyers, an invitation to the execution, a certificate of witness to the execution, and the defendants&#039; directions for the disposition of their bodies.</p>
                                 <p>Frederick Matson, of Pennsylvania State University, donated this collection to the Library in 1978.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


